value.0: "Oh, you are back, <master/mistress>. Trip is so pleased to see you again. You must have need of Trip's skills, shall I follow you?"
"Trip does not want to stay here, good <master/mistress>. Please do not leave me here for long."
"I will try to help you as best I can, <FirstName>... I mean master."
"Elf twins... yummy!"
"This part of the city makes Trip feel uncomfortable. Too clean. Too rich."
"Graves and tombs; one of the very best places for a hungry rat to hide!"
"What dark, secrets might this hidden passage hold? Trip is curious."
"That merchant over there is selling dead rats! Trip should scare him and say I come in revenge for my kin!"
"This tavern is too clean. There must be a proper dive in this city for Trip to drink at."
"Trip should make an offering at Veragok's shrine. Or maybe just a prayer. Cheaper that way."
"That man is more nervous than Trip. What is his problem?"
"Undead taste so terrible! Makes Trip feel woozy in the tummy."
"So you own this dump now? Trip likes it. Very homey."

Comment.value: in Silvertongue manor after meeting Ellysia

value.0: "Nice place, nice girl; what does ugly Becket have that Trip doesn't?"
"These goblins have very tasty ears. Trip wonders if there might be a market for them as a nice, light snack."
"Mmm... smells like dead things in here. Can we stay for a while? Trip likes the ambiance."
"This is the kind of place a rat could retire and really feel at home."
"Lots of lovely stuff in here to steal... I mean look at. Heh heh."
"Kobolds are so stupid. Trip doesn't know why anyone would befriend a kobold."
"Trip hates dwarves! Well, dark dwarves. Not dwarves with burning heads. Actually Trip would like to see some dark dwarves with flaming heads!"
"This is the castle? Stinks of civilization. When you win, we put in walls and make a maze in here."
"For such a rich fiend, ugly Becket's home is not so grand."
"Trip is always ready to speak to you, fearless leader."
"Say it isn't so, <master/mistress>! Do not abandon poor Trip to the hostile monsters! And Trip includes the people of the keep in that description!"
"Trip does not want to be left here! Oh, do not be long, cruel <master/mistress>!"
"Then I will go and hide out in the Mossy Tree. Trip hopes you will come and find him there soon."
"Did Trip do something wrong?"
"<Master/Mistress> likes the sound and feel of explosions? And people think Trip is strange!"
"Much better than hearing, 'click, KABOOM'. Trip will do his best."
"Moving quickly is what gets good folks like us killed! But Trip will follow <master/mistress>, even in foolishness."
"Trip always wants to stay in the shadows, so this is an easy thing!"
"That is just silly. That is what Trip does best!"
"Unlocking locksies and chewing on rings, these are a few of Trip's favorite things!"
"Trip did not mean to smell bad, if this is what brings you to change my pace."
"Trip will do as kind <master/mistress> suggests."
"Trip is not meant for making such bold melee! I will do my best, but I make no promises!"
"Trip does not like to attack. Always better to run or hide."
"Trip is always happy to take advice from <master/mistress> on how to dress."
"Trip will sniff at it and gnaw at it and see if I can discover what it is!"
"I shall do my best to remain hidden. That is where Trip prefers to be, always."
"Talk? What do you want Trip to talk about?"
"Is there anything else humble Trip can do for you, <master/mistress>?"
"Trip could not do that, no. After all, if Trip was not beholden to <master/mistress>, Trip would not be here in these gods-forsaken lands of the north."
"Trip owes <master/mistress> his life, and so I will follow you, even into such danger. Trip is pleased to serve you, <master/mistress>."
"I am not dead yet, so Trip figures that is a good sign. Always good not to be dead yet."
"You want anything else from Trip?"
"Trip would like to rest soon. Not that I am tired, but sleep is always good."
"Now why you have to go and interrupt Trip's daydream with such nonsense? I was chewing on a nice, ripe, bloated carcass... yummy, yummy."
"What? You're talking about the voices in Trip's head, aren't you? Well, there are no voices... so stop talking to me... all of you!"
"Trip has a headache, probably from too much sun. Maybe we should travel only at night and sleep all day."
"There is a thorn in Trip's paw, and it really hurts. Wait... ah... that's better!"
"Trip is fine. I am not hurt, or mangled, or chewed on, or digested, or anything!"
"Darkness! Darkness all around! The shadows have come for Trip and soon he will be dead!"
"Almost dying... <master/mistress>! Trip... needs... healer!"
"Close to dying... <master/mistress>! Trip... needs... healer!"
"Dying... <master/mistress>! Trip... needs... healer!"
"Trip thinks he might have eaten a bit of rotting meat. I do not feel so good."
"Trip feels sick. I know I am always diseased, but now I feel more so than before."
Trip blinks rapidly at your question. "Trip has high aspirations. I would like to make a big dungeon and fill it with monsters and traps and spells and treasures and make people pay to go into it."
"When you are the adventurer, the monsters try to kill you. When you are the monster, adventurers try to kill you. Trip is tired of being both."
"If Trip ran a famous adventure place that both monsters and adventurers wanted to be, nobody would want to be killing him!"
Trip shrugs, "Maybe Trip can find some crazy wizard to help me. Or profit sharing."
"Yes, Trip will offer monsters a split of loot from people they kill and Trip keeps the rest, plus the entrance fee."
"To attract the most attention, Trip thinks it would be best to have it underneath a large city. I will call it something simple and easy to remember... maybe, Undercity!"

Comment.value: trip has told the third part of his story

value.0: "If you are an adventurer, you have to go and search around and find monsters to battle and sometimes those monsters have no treasure."
"If monsters and treasure were all in one challenging place, Trip thinks people would pay lots of gold to go there, in hopes of proving themselves and finding a big treasure trove."
"Trip always wants to know what good <master/mistress> thinks."
"Trip has no idea what you are talking about, <master/mistress>. I think you mean you would not like such a place, but that is alright. I think there are many out there who would like it."
"Trip cannot please everyone, but he hopes to please enough to make me lots of gold."
"We should get going again. Staying in one spot for very long makes Trip nervous."
"Trip is pleased that you like his idea, and I think such a big undertaking would need more than just Trip's efforts."
"When that day comes, perhaps Trip and <FirstName> will work together in equality. Then Trip can stop calling you <master/mistress>."
"Trip has heard that before. Trip is not surprised that <master/mistress> would not like his idea much, but I think there are many out there who would like it."
"Which part: the fleas, the overwhelming desire to chew on dead things, the voices in my head, or the way everybody always stares at me? "
He shrugs. "Trip loves being a wererat." Scratching furriously, he turns away.
"Life was so lonely before the voices. Trip likes being a wererat, for the voices more than anything. Of course the voices didn't start until I met you."

"Not really. I suppose Trip had the fleas before I became a wererat. People often stared at me as a human, since I was so ugly. Chewing on dead things is new, though. And the voices started when I met you."
"Yes. Trip was enjoying his travels through the countryside, frightening the locals and eating their chi... I mean livestock."
"Then you and the flaming dwarf and cathead caught me. I don't know how well you remember it, but the image is burned into Trip's memory."

Comment.value: trip has told the second part of his story

value.0: "Apparently you had been paid to find me, though I doubt it could have been much, coming from farmers."
"And then you took Trip's treasure, which is why you allowed Trip to live, was it not?"
"You did find Trip with treasure. That was why Trip was allowed to live, was it not?"
"Yes, you have love for strange creatures, which causes some problems for Trip, though I was happy for it when you allowed me to live."
"Yes, you seem to enjoy these heroic moments more than Trip would like. But I was glad for your heroic nature when you let me live."

"And Trip is very useful, isn't he, <master/mistress>? You chose me over others in the group, and I am thankful. I shall continue to be useful to you. Trip shall find you more things and make you rich and powerful."
"Oh, <master/mistress>, Trip has changed his ways. Trip is the soul of kindness and love when it comes to doing your will. I will feed the hungry and clothe the poor, if that is your wish."
"And that is why Trip has such deep care for you, <master/mistress>! Trip has the same love for pretty things as you do, so we work well together."
"Oh, and kind <master/mistress>, Trip will grovel at your feet for as long as you wish. Trip is humbled by your mighty presence and simply wishes to bask in your noble glow."
"You should not be worried about Trip's loyalty. You are such a good <master/mistress>. Trip hardly feels the yoke and whip as you lead me into places too dangerous to imagine!"
"You... you call Trip a friend? You are such a good <master/mistress>. Trip hardly feels the yoke and whip as you lead me into places too dangerous to imagine!"
He sniffles. "Trip thinks we should get going now. You have many important things for Trip to help you with. We should go do them now."
"And you are such a good <master/mistress>. Trip hardly feels the yoke and whip as you lead me into places too dangerous to imagine!"
"Like this place. Why, Trip would never have come here in a thousand years... would never even have dreamed of chasing after a beholder, and yet here I am."
"Watch what names you call me, Trip, or we shall play a game of cat and mouse."
"I wanted to kill you then just about as bad as I've ever wanted to kill anyone."
"What do you mean, I do not like it? Trip loves it! Life is much more interesting now, especially around you. Of course, the voices didn't start talking to me until I met you."
"You do not know what it is like to be ugly and shunned by people, <FirstName>. It might come as a shock to you, but Trip was not always the cute and lovable man you know now."

Comment.value: set first part of tale told

value.0: "Trip was once an ugly, selfish man. Small, pockmarked and hated by all, I became bitter and self-absorbed. I was a petty thief, with few friends to call my own."
"I was cowardly then, and much more selfish than I am now. Truly, I was at the bottom of the cesspool called humanity."
"That is because you did not know the old, horrible Trip. I am much better than I once was. I was at the bottom of the cesspool called humanity."
"I was cowardly then, and much more selfish than I am now. Truly, I was at the bottom of the cesspool called humanity."
"I was cowardly then, and much more selfish than I am now. Truly, I was at the bottom of the cesspool called humanity."
"Then I stole some important documents from the thieves' guildmaster, who never liked Trip anyway, and he sent a few wererat assassins after me."
"They caught up to Trip as he was about to deliver the documents to the local authorities, who had paid Trip well."
"How I escaped was a combination of luck and quick thinking. Trip recovered from the ambush and managed to evade everything but the first bite."

"I burst into the magistrate's office with four wererats on my tail... well, not literally, since Trip did not have a tail yet. The office happened to be filled with a number of guards, who leapt to attack us."

"I screamed and curled up into a little ball. The guards must have dismissed me as unimportant, for they attacked my enemies and while they fought, I managed to crawl out the door and slip down into the sewers."
"Ha, you made a funny! Tale... drag... oh, did you not mean to make a funny? Trip will hurry then."
"The disease gripped me while I was hidden in the tunnels. I don't know how fast it normally infects a person, but my body was weak and it didn't take too long."
"When Trip transformed into a wererat, I decided that my old life was over. I discarded my human guise, my human name and left the city never to return."
"It does not matter who I was, or what I was. I am Trip. I am a wererat. People can deal with it, or just leave me alone! Trip is tired of talking. Let's go find a bone to gnaw on!"
"Yes. You see how much stronger and better Trip has become? It is like I am a whole different person."
"That bite was the best thing that ever happened to Trip. Oh sure, I did not think so at the time, but in retrospect I am now a much happier rat than I ever was a man."

"You have had some experience with people reacting negatively to your presence, but not the same as me. It might come as a shock to you, but Trip was not always the cute and lovable man you know now."

value.0: "Trip... must not... must not listen to the voice! Must not betray my friend. Get out of my head, stupid voice!"

LinkComment.value: if PC has heard Trip's story about Undercity

value.0: "Why not you, <master/mistress>? You treat me like your slave. Go fetch me magic items, Trip! Open that lock, disarm that trap, well, TRIP IS TIRED OF BEING YOUR SLAVE!"
"Wouldn't you like to know, <master/mistress>! You treat me like your slave. Go fetch me magic items, Trip! Open that lock, disarm that trap, well, TRIP IS TIRED OF BEING YOUR SLAVE!"
"The voice is right. He whispers to me, and tells me how you will lead me to my death. You don't really care for Trip, you just use him to get what you want."
"You would just leave me for dead, when my job is done! No... no, <master/mistress> would not do this to Trip! I will not listen to this voice. I will not listen to his horrid lies!"
"That is what you would like. To have more monsters come, so they can eat Trip! Well, Trip will not be here anymore! Trip is leaving, now!"
"Undercity! <Master/Mistress> remembers our dreams! <FirstName> is really Trips friend! I will not listen to the evil voice anymore!"
<StartCheck>[Success]</Start> "You would hurt Trip? The voice was right! You cannot be trusted. Trip must leave now!"
<StartCheck>[Success]</Start> "You would let Trip be the master? No... no, instead of a master, we should be... friends... equals... partners!"
<StartCheck>[Failed]</Start> "It... it is too strong... no... <master/mistress> tells us lies. We must not listen! We must only trust the voice."
"Trip must flee. Trip must run and hide somewhere far from here. Trip will go south... yes... south to safety!"
"Trip will not be bossed around by you anymore! I am leaving and you cannot stop me!"
"You... you would allow Trip to flee? You would let me go, even when you need me the most?"

Comment.value: Trip quits party and runs away (destroy self)

value.0: "Sorry... sorry... Trip cannot stay. Trip must flee. Sorry."
"Is your mind as weak as your body, lad? The voice speaks to me too, but it is easy to resist. It is our enemy, the Masked Man. Don't let him weaken you."
"This voice, it is most compelling, but you must not give up hope, Trip. Listen to us, not the voice!"
"Trip, I can hear the voice too. It is only the mind games of our enemy, the Masked Man. He is an illithid and such creatures always attack the mind. You must fight him!"
<StartCheck>[Success]</Start> "It... it is too strong... no! I will not betray, <FirstName>! I will not! I will ignore you, like I ignore all the other voices!"
"Oh, <FirstName>! Trip is so sorry. I did not mean to think of betraying you. The voice kept whispering in my brain, right from the time we entered the cave."
"Let us go and face our enemy! Trip shall rip out its throat and gnaw at its intestines!"
"Oh, you are back, <master/mistress>. Trip is so pleased to see you again. You must have need of Trip's skills, shall I follow you?"
"Oh, you are back, <master/mistress>. Trip is so pleased to see you again. You must have need of Trip's skills, shall I follow you?"
"The voices in Trip's head were right. Oh, woe is me. Trip has been abandoned."
"Trip is so pleased. The voices said you had abandoned Trip, but I did not give up hope!"
"Wait, wait, wait! Trip has something to tell you, but you move so quickly, never letting Trip have time to breathe!"
"Oh, of course, <master/mistress>. It is not as though Trip would have anything important to say. You just continue on with your more important duties."
"Maybe the <master/mistress> has a flea in <his/her> loincloth and that is why <he/she> has such a short temper today?"
"Trip wonders if this is all really worth it. Maybe I should just slit my throat and have done."
"What? Would you make Trip grovel for your forgiveness too? Are you so cruel?"
"Trip grovels for your forgiveness, <master/mistress>! There is no excuse for my awful behavior."

Comment.value:
inside Yenna's tower, not in same room as Yenna, but after talking to her.
create Bracers of Limited Functionality on Trip

value.0: "These are funny-looking things, do you not think so, <master/mistress>?"
"Yenna, the pretty smelling woman, she gave them to Trip. Very nice of her, yes."
"Why is it that everytime Trip finds something, it goes to the <master/mistress>? I could get very bitter about such things, if I was that kind of person."
Trip howls in anguish. "Oh, <master/mistress>! You are too kind to Trip. I am filth! I am unworthy of your kind benevolence! I did not know you were only looking out for Trip's well-being!"
"Take the bracers, <master/mistress> and do not give them back to unworthy Trip! Whip me with the cat-o-nines and teach me humility! Bad Trip! Bad, bad Trip!"
Trip sulks. "Yes, <master/mistress>. Trip is sure you will know what best to do with them. I am just a stupid servant."
"Well, I am almost certain she meant for me to have them. She left them sitting on a table, in open view, and she turned her back on the table a number of times while speaking to you."
"How much more evidence could you ask for? Trip was the soul of caution, but she made it too easy. So easy that I knew immediately that she was giving Trip permission to take them."
"That is true, Trip is very wise in these things. If she did not want me to have them, she would have been far more careful. She is, after all, a very powerful mage."

Comment.value: put bracers on Trip. Mark this conversation as done.

value.0: "Trip knew you would see reason! Thank you, <master/mistress>. You are too kind to Trip."
"Trip will return them immediately <master/mistress>. Trip did not mean to give offense." Trip bows to you, muttering angrily under his breath.
He flips them around in his hands, eyeing them from different angles. "That is the conclusion Trip was going to draw."
"This room looks very familiar to Trip! Not that I have been in this room before, but in one very much like it indeed."
"Trip will shut up, then. Trip knows how to be quiet, yes he does! Why, one time Trip was silent for a year! Or maybe it was only a month. Maybe less. A couple hours, anyways."
"Well, one of my old guildmasters was a real paranoid type. Maybe because we kept trying to kill him. Anyways, he had rigged his hideout with all sorts of special traps."
"He had special powder-filled crystals that would be crushed and explode when he pulled the lever that closed the doors. The setup to this is so similar, Trip finds it eerie."
"Trip thinks that luring the manticore in here might be the harder part."
"How would Trip know? Maybe if we look around we can find something like that."

value.0: "Trip likes this Thaddeus fellow. He has a black, twisted mind and excellent taste in magical amulets."
"Did you not see the one hanging around his neck? It was nice and shiny, like a big metal sign saying, 'Steal me, Trip. I don't belong here. Take me with you!'"
"Or maybe that was just one of the voices in my head, I'm not sure. Whatever, it was quite tricky getting the amulet from around his neck without anyone seeing me."

Comment.value: give PC amulet of Natural Armor +2

value.0: "Lucky thing that I'm so good at my job, or Trip wouldn't have this nice little present for <master/mistress>."
He shrugs. "Trip steals things he thinks are worth stealing and tries not to get caught by stealing worthless junk. Besides, the amulet definitely tasted of magic."
"Trip is hurt by your wild accusations! I don't keep everything I steal! I give most of it to you. Sometimes <master/mistress> gives stuff to help Trip, so I give stuff back."
"Trip likes to please the <master/mistress>."
"How else would Trip know if the amulet is made of good materials? Trip just tries to please the <master/mistress>."
"<StartAction>[Sigh]</Start> Trip just hoped you would be pleased I stole from an evil person, rather than a good one. The amulet definitely tasted of magic."
"Trip hopes you would be pleased with him. The amulet definitely tasted of magic."

value.0: Trip suddenly bursts into song. "You take the rod in hand, you slip the end knob out, you push the button here in, and then you shake it all about..."
"Eek! Trip did not mean for that to happen! It was an accident, <master/mistress>! Trip finds this magic stick hidden in goblin room."
"It was the voices; they told me I should play with it! Oh, curse those foolish voices!"
"Well, Trip was going to just give it to you, but I wanted to try it first... I mean I was just... it was just an accident. How should Trip know that playing with a stick would make lightning?"
"Um... no, no, not voices... um, did Trip say that? I did not mean that... I meant... it was just an accident. How should Trip know that playing with a stick would make lightning?"
"Yes, <master/mistress>. Trip is sorry." Trip hangs his head and heaves a great sigh as he hands over the rod.
"Maybe you buy Trip a new magic ring with gold from rod? I love rings, because they can make you invisible, or harder to hit, or regenerate body parts, and they taste good too!"
"Oh, Trip will not eat it. I just like to taste it and chew on it and stick it on the end of my tongue and pretend that my tongue is an extra finger."
Trip pouts, but doesn't open his mouth again.
"I can hardly wait for Trip's new magic ring! It will be... precious to me."
"I think that Trip is in the right group then, if he is so strange."
"Sorry, <master/mistress>. Trip will try to control his enthusiasm from now on."
"Yes, yes, Trip is a good servant," Trip says sullenly, pouting to himself.

Comment.value: For a trigger in the dungeon, after the hobgoblin is killed.

value.0: "This place reminds Trip of the good old days. Back when I was a young thief and me and my pals would just go out and kill monsters and loot their treasure for no real purpose."
"Well, Trip just thought you would want to know about something. It must not be important. Trip will just shut his mouth and sulk for a while now."
"It is just that, well... I am rather disappointed in the treasure we are finding so far. I mean we killed the big, bad hobgoblin, and did you really think he was so tough?"
"I mean, he hurt all those soldiers and stuff and maybe they weakened him or something, but I expected him to put up more of a fight."
"Well... he was tough compared to a small goblin, but not so tough compared to a big dragon!"
"Well, Trip did not fight a dragon himself, but one of the voices in my head was telling me about a dragon fight that sounded so scary, it made this fight seem boring."
"And the hobgoblin didn't have much treasure, except for this one thing that Trip found. Not like a dragon has treasure, that's for certain!"
"Oh, right. It is just that I found this ring on the hobgoblin's toe, and I thought maybe you might have missed it."
"Trip was just going to keep it and not say anything, but Trip was not knowing what the ring would do and he thought maybe he should give it to <master/mistress>."

"Trip would not want to put the ring on and then find himself turned into a frog, or teleported into the middle of an ocean, or crushed by falling rocks, or any of the things that a magic ring might decide to do."
"That would be a wise idea. We would not want something bad to happen to the <master/mistress> and leave poor Trip all alone."
"That would be very bad for Trip... I mean for you."
"No, no, no! Is that what Trip says? That was a bad thing that the voices said to do! Trip would not listen to them and decided to give you the ring!"
"But do be careful with it, <master/mistress>. Trip heard an old mage once say that a ring is like a sharp sword, if you don't know how to use it, you'll probably lose a few toes."
"Trip is not sure what that means, but I have been extra careful ever since I heard it. Trip needs all his toes."

Comment.value: in the Hermit's house on the way to the secret door.

value.0: "Hee, hee, hee! I can't believe they missed my amulet! I thought they would have stripped it off of me with my other equipment."
"Trip does not care what anybody says, I need this amulet. Trip would give up a million gold to keep his wonderful amulet."
"It is the filth that keeps people from discovering the truth about Trip's treasure!"
"I got it the same day Trip became a wererat. I do not wish to talk about that experience right now, but I can tell you about how I found my amulet, if you wish to hear it."
"Then I shall not bother you with my tale. Trip is simply pleased to keep his magic talisman."
"I do not have to tell you anything, if you do not truly care to hear it. It is your choice."
"Perpetit... pepitant... whatever you try to say, I am not sure, but I will nod my head and pretend understanding. I will tell my tale."
"I was huddled in fear in a sewer, hiding from the thieves who hunted me. A fever raged in my brain, the fever of lycanthropy. My stomach ached, my head burned and I needed food, badly."
"I saw some movement and realized it was a rat. A nice big juicy rat! It came towards me, sniffing to see if Trip was edible. How foolish it was!"
"I lashed out my newly clawed and hairy paw, grabbed the rat, and tore it apart with my sharp fangs. The taste of the blood was like nothing I had ever enjoyed before."
"Ick, why ruin perfectly good rat flesh with cooking. The salt is a good idea though. Trip might have to try that sometime."
"Sorry, Trip gets carried away when he thinks of tearing the flesh of of small, furry animals... mmm."
"Well, I prayed to the gods to protect me and when I clasped the rat skull, I felt like I was... more hidden. The thieves that were hunting me never found me, thanks to that skull."
"I don't know whether there was divine intervention, or maybe I just got lucky and found a rat with a magic skull. But Trip takes no chances and gives gold to shrines of Veragok, god of shadows."
"You would be well served to remember that and go to the temple in the keep as soon as we get there."
"Oh yes, it is powerful magic for Trip. It is Trip's lucky talisman. If it were not for this amulet, Trip would have died years ago."
"It is a filthy and disgusting object."
"You know, there are many shadows in Mistress Death's realm, but they are not the shadows that comfort and protect... no they are not!"
"Trip notices things moving in those shadows. Things with nasty, sharp teeth. Trip is glad you brings me back. I'll just come with you then, right?"
"Trip thanks you <master/mistress>. You are such a good <master/mistress>."
"Oh no! Do not leave Trip here, <master/mistress>! I beg of you; do not make me stay here long!"
"Eek! I don't wanna bite you and you don't wanna get any diseases, so just stay away from Trip!"
"What... what is that smell? Like the stench of death... oh... wait... that's me. Never mind."
"You know, Jaboli, for all of your arrogance, Trip thinks you are not so bad."
"I am so glad I meet with your approval. I care so deeply for your opinion," Jaboli says, her voice steeped in sarcasm.
"Trip is glad you care. Trip was thinking something and wanted to surprise you with my thoughts."
"That your head contains thoughts at all is of great surprise to me."
"Yes, you and I are very similar! We are both intelligent and furry!"
"I really don't like where this is going."
"I was just thinking that if I could just give you a little nibble, then you would make a lovely wererat-cat girlfriend!"
"Ew! Not in a million years! If the Gods came down and threatened to destroy the entire universe unless I did as you say, I would allow us all to die!"
"I'll give you some time to get used to the idea. You'll come around."
"You alright, Jaboli? Trip is concerned."
"Of course I am alright. What would make you think otherwise?"
"It is just that Trip hears you making little choking noises and thinks maybe you are choking up a hairball."
"A hairball?!? Why you mangy, little rat! I am not a cat! I don't get hairballs!"
"Then why were you making that sound? It sounded much like a cat I once had when I was a human. It coughed up hairballs all the time, just before it died."
"Well, it's not a hairball! I was simply laughing about something."
"What was so funny? Trip could use a good laugh."
"None of your business, wererat!"
"You aren't even going to tell Trip why you were laughing? Why not?"
"Because it was a private observation! Besides, you wouldn't even understand."
"Trip knows what he understands. Jaboli has hairballs and is too proud to admit it. Maybe soon Jaboli dies like Trip's cat, then we see who doesn't understand stuff!"
"You are an annoying little rat. I shall ignore you, now."
"You are always so sad, Kaidala. You shouldn't be sad. Trip thinks you are quite beautiful, yes!"
"Trip, you're just saying that because of the nice things I said to you."
"No, no, no! Trip thinks you are quite pretty, like a gem with a small flaw. The gem is still pretty and and can be cherished as much as any other beautiful thing."
"That... that is a very nice thing to say, Trip. Thank you."
"Look, Trip has found this and wants you to have it. It is also very pretty." Trip hands her a ring.
"Oh Trip, that is so sweet! I must admit, I never saw this side of you before."
"It is pretty, like you! Wait, what are you doing? Don't put it on, it will..."
"What is happening to me?" Kaidala collapses.

value.0: "Then why did you give it to me?"
"Because Trip knows it is flawed beauty, like Kaidala. Pretty to look at, but can kill you real quick."
"Ugh... keep your little present, Trip."
"Sheesh, Trip will never understand some people!"
"You are both a nymph and a druid, Kaidala, so Trip is thinking you know lots about nature."
"Yes, that is one subject that I would consider myself an expert. Why do you ask?"
"People... normal people, that is... well, they call me a freak... an unatural monstrosity... and I was just wondering, do you think I am unnatural?"
"That is a difficult question, Trip. On one hand, you have a disease. Disease is a perversion of nature, one that druids will usually fight to destroy."
"So you think I should be destroyed?!?"
"Not at all, though I would cure you if I could... and if you wanted me to. But what I was going to say is that sometimes a disease can lead to the creation of something better... stronger."
"So you don't wish to destroy Trip? You think Trip is better than he was?"

"I don't know what you were before, but you do seem to use your abilities to keep yourself alive. That you refuse to change to other forms makes me believe that you find strength you didn't have before."
"I... I used to hate myself. I had a weak chin, a pocked face, and was very disliked by... well, pretty much everyone."
"I can see how this form would be... um... better."
"Do you think so? That is very kind of you to say. So would you like to give Trip a little kiss?"
"Oh... um... it's just that fur makes me... sneeze... ah choo!"
"I understand. Trip will find someone, someday. Thank you for your kind words though."
"Calibast, you are very brave. How is it that you can rush into a battle and not worry about getting hurt?"
"I am strong enough to withstand many blows, so I figure that if I kill my opponents quickly, I can survive whatever attacks they land."
"Ah, Trip was thinking perhaps you were not smart enough to know about danger, with your head on fire all the time."
"You had better watch what you say about my mind, lad. You don't seem all that bright yourself."
"That's not what Trip meant, exactly. It is just that you never used some of the strategies that <FirstName> uses. Maybe because your brain is hot, you lose temper easily."
"I'm about to begin losing my temper right now!"
"That's what Trip meant. Your brain is sizzling in your skull and you lose all rational thought."
"Get this filthy, little coward away from me, <FirstName>!"
"That's what Trip was saying. I was just wondering why he... acts so explosively."
"Trip didn't mean any harm in it. I was just wondering why he... acts so explosively."
"I act that way because of little cretins like you, Ratboy, who don't know how to keep their mouths shut."
"Trip will be quiet now. Your eyeballs look like they are ready to burst into flames too."
"Blast it, Calibast! Your flaming head makes it very tricky for Trip to avoid unwanted attention!"
"You really think that a giant wererat would be ignored if my head wasn't on fire?"
"It's called blending, dwarf. Trip is short compared to everyone else, so if I just hunch my shoulders a bit and keep my head down, people overlook me in a crowd."
"An azer is not the same as a dwarf! Boy, whatever pity I ever felt for you is shortly being used up. Why don't you go gnaw on a bone?"
"Where is this bone? Does it have flesh on it? Wait... you... you are tricking Trip! The bone I should gnaw on is your leg!"
"Sorry, <master/mistress>. Trip only tries to keep you safe."
"You'd better look to your own skin and leave the protection up to me."
"Maybe if he soaks his head in a bucket of water it puts out the flames. Then he could be like a normal dwarf."
"What?!? I'll soak your head in a bucket of water for about an hour and see how many fleas float to the surface!"
"See? Trip makes a perfectly innocent suggestion and the dwarf explodes like a fireball!"
"I AM NOT A DWARF! I'M A FLAMING AZER; LEARN THE DIFFERENCE!"
"Oh... sorry, <master/mistress>."
"Just stay out of my reach, ratman."
"That has yet to be proven. There a world of difference."
"Not much if you'd take a nice long bath."
"That little carrion-eater had better stay away from my legs. I don't need any filthy diseases!"
"Trip would chew on your head, but the meat would be too cooked for my tastes!"
"Just keep the filthy creature away from me."
"Sorry, master. Trip will try to do better for you."
"Not yet. I will come back for you."
"Yes. Please follow me."
"Never mind."
"I think we need to part ways."
"No, never mind."
"Wait here until I return."
"I need to go."

value.0: "I want to change your tactics."

"I want you to disarm any traps that you see."
"I want to move faster and not bother with searching or stealth."
"I need you to be stealthy right now."
"Don't help me if I fail to open a locked door or chest."
"Help me if I fail to open a locked door or chest."
"I want to change the distance you stay away from me."
"Stay a long distance away."
"Keep a medium distance."
"Stay close."
"Go ahead and attack as soon as you see enemies."
"Defend me and don't attack until I do."
"I want to adjust your equipment."
"Can you identify my equipment?"
"I need you to blend into the shadows."
"What was it you wanted to say earlier?"
"Let's stop and talk a moment."
"We're done talking."
"No, nothing else."
"I want you to stop calling me <master/mistress>."
"How is everything?"
"Do you have plans for what you're going to do after all this?"
"Why would you want to do that?"
"How would you get all the monsters in there?"
"Profit sharing?"
"What would you call your dungeon?"
"Why would people pay to go into such a place?"
"Do you want my opinion on your idea?"
"It wouldn't be much fun. Far too linear and combat-oriented."
"Good plan. If you need any help getting started, just ask."
"I'd love to help you with that. I think it would be quite successful."
"You're doomed to failure."
"What is it like being a wererat?"
"Suddenly I don't want to know..."
"Let's talk about the voices."
"Me?"
"Are you sure that's from being a wererat?"
"Me?"

"We were hoping to find you with a bunch of treasure."
"We were more interested in finding out about you."
"They spoke of your atrocities, so we thought it was worth doing."
"Your *treasure* was a horde of refuse. I just figured you might be useful."
"An enemy deserves mercy, if they change their ways, which you promised to do."
"You lived because you paid us off."
"I let you live because you groveled so pathetically."
"Sometimes I wonder about your loyalty, Trip."
"You are a good friend, Trip."
"You aren't too bad a companion, Trip."
"So you don't like being a wererat?"
"Me?"
"Why don't you ever assume your human form?"
"Now you are just a cowardly, ugly, selfish rat."
"I'm not seeing much of a change here."

"How did you survive that meeting?"
"Hurry up, this tale is starting to drag."
"What happened next?"
"You betrayed your master?"

"What is the voice saying, Trip?"

"Trip, what's happening?"

"You had better stop yelling, Trip, before you draw more monsters to us."

"Quit complaining, Trip."
"What do you want, Trip?"

"First tell me where you got that new belt."
"Here." <StartAction>[Help Trip loosen his *new* belt.]</Start>
"Where did you find the belt?"

"I would like to see the belt, please."
"You have to return this, Trip."
"Now, Trip!"
"Where did you get those bracers?"
"Give them to me."

"I don't like your attitude, ratman! Give them to me, now!"

"She gave them to you?"

"Fine, you can keep them."
"Give them back to her, now!"
"Those are bracers."
"I really don't care."
"How is it familiar?"
"Tell me what you know, then."

"Do you think there might be crystals here?"

"I can't stand him."
"What do you mean? What amulets?"
"Is that all you managed to steal?"
"I'm surprised you didn't keep it for yourself."

"Trip, you shouldn't steal from people in the keep!"
"Ha, ha! I like having you around, Trip."
